visa_types.documents_required:
Study visa (full time, master degree)
- Passport (time period between the date of its  issue and date of visa application must not exceed 10 years and passport must  be valid for at least 3 months as of the end date of the planned trip);
- Invitation letter issued by the Office of  Citizenship and Migration Affairs (OCMA) (
www.pmlp.gov.lv (https://www.pmlp.gov.lv/lv)
)
- E-Visa application form for Latvian National  Visa (D) filled in on the Latvian Embassy to Kazakhstan website, printed out  and personally signed in relevant boxes of the application form marked by a  “signature” note. Visa application form is available by this link  (
https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/ (https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/)
);
- One photo on the white background, 70% should be  covered by the face; photo should be attached to the application form by the  Applicant;
- Health insurance for a period of 90 days from  the date of arrival to Latvia, insurance coverage amount should be not less  than 42 600 EUR;
- Proof of travel ticket booking;
- A written confirmation from a University or  other officially accredited educational institution regarding the matriculation  of the student;
- A document confirming the envisaged place of  residence;
- Study contract (copy);
- Bank account statement for the last three  months, minimum account balance for studies is 7440 EUR. In case of sponsorship  – proof of it (e.g.  financial documents,  a letter of guarantee) another person is paying for your studies ;
- Other certificates and supporting documents  relevant to the case (e.g. work experience certificate, IELTS/ TOEFL diploma,  etc.).
- (Post-graduate students (Master degree, PhD) and  exchange students are exempted from payment of the State fee)
Erasmus and other Exchange Students
- Passport (time period between the date of its  issue and date of visa application must not exceed 10 years and passport must  be valid for at least 3 months as of the end date of the planned trip);
- Invitation letter issued by the Office of  Citizenship and Migration Affairs (OCMA) (
www.pmlp.gov.lv (https://www.pmlp.gov.lv/lv)
);
- Reference letter from home University;
- E-Visa application form for Latvian National  Visa D filled in on the website of the Latvian Embassy to Kazakhstan, printed  out and signed in relevant boxes of the application form marked by “signature”  note. Visa application form is available by this link  (
https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/ (https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/)
);
- One photo, on the white background, 70% should  be covered by the face; photo should be attached to the application form by the  Applicant;
- Health insurance for the period of stay in  Latvia from the date of arrival, insurance coverage amount should be not less  than 42 600 EUR;
- Proof of ticket booking;
- Proof of sufficient financial means in the form  of a letter from the home university stating that the student has been granted  a scholarship. The minimum monthly amount for stay in Latvia for students is  620 EUR. If the university’s sponsorship letter states a smaller amount,  additional proof is required indicating the availability of the missing amount  for the entire period of stay in Latvia.
(Students participating in Erasmus+ program are exempted  from payment of State fee.)
Work visa (work agreement)
- Passport (time period between the date of its  issue and date of visa application must not exceed 10 years and passport must  be valid for at least 3 months as of the end date of the planned trip);
- Invitation letter issued by the Office of  Citizenship and Migration Affairs (OCMA) (
www.pmlp.gov.lv (https://www.pmlp.gov.lv/lv)
);
- E-Visa application form for Latvian National  Visa D filled in on the website of the Latvian Embassy to Kazakhstan, printed  out and signed in relevant boxes of the application form marked by “signature”  note. Visa application form is available by this link (
https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/ (https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/)
);
- One photo, on white background, 70% should be  covered by the face; photo should be attached to the application form by the  Applicant;
- Health insurance for the period of stay in  Latvia from the date of arrival, insurance coverage amount should be not less  than 42 600 EUR;
- Work agreement (signed by employer and  employee);
- Proof of flight ticket or booking;
- Proof of the accommodation for your stay in  Latvia
- Proof of the monthly financial
means (https://www.pmlp.gov.lv/en/necessary-subsistence-0)
. Bank certificate and statement of available finance resources provided for the last 3 months from the same bank account;
- Optional - Job reference from your previous  working place;
- Optional - Other documents, e.g. certificates  proving qualification, statements from previous working places etc.
Visa Applications for Residence Permit (only with the OCMA  decision granting the rights of residence)
- Passport (time period between the date of its  issue and date of visa application must not exceed 10 years and passport must  be valid for at least 3 months as of the end date of the planned trip);
- Copy of the Decision of the Office of  Citizenship and Migration Affairs proving the Applicant has been granted the  rights of residence in Latvia;
- E-Visa application form for Latvian National  Visa D filled in on the website of the Latvian Embassy to Kazakhstan, printed  out and signed in relevant boxes of the application form marked by “signature”  note. Visa application form is available by this link  (
https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/ (https://epak.pmlp.gov.lv/NVIS.EService001.WebSite/)
);
- One photo on white background, 70% should be  covered by the face; photo should be attached to the application form by the  Applicant;
- Health insurance for the 90 days period from the  date of arrival to Latvia, insurance coverage amount should be not less than 42  600 EUR;
- Visa fee is 60 EUR (Minors younger than 16 are  exempted of State fee payment)

